{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_28","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6260-fails-javac-compile-net.minidev-accessors-smart-2.4.3-2af4ad77\n\nThe most likely failing stage is artifact resolution / coverage collection, not a Java source incompatibility in the generated tests. The first failing Gradle run in `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T16-21-57-460820Z.log` shows `:compileTestJava` failed because Maven Central does not provide `net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3` as a main jar (`Could not find accessors-smart-2.4.3.jar`). The preserved branch contains a workaround in `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/build.gradle` to compile against the published `sources` classifier instead, and later reruns in `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T16-24-53-330207Z.log` and `human-intervention-logs/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-06T16-25-33-748676Z.log` are successful. The generated test results under `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/build/test-results/test/` and `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/test-results-native/test/` show all 5 tests passing.\n\nThe workflow still ended in failure because coverage/metrics could not work with the missing main artifact. `build/tests/net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3/5108b76808b592e1a62eee18f3f9daf3.out` fails while creating `:jacocoTestReport` with `No eligible artifacts found on the classpath for net.minidev:accessors-smart:2.4.3`, and `stats/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, and `code_coverage_percent: 0.0`.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Review the preserved branch and decide whether the `sources`-classifier workaround in `tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/build.gradle` should be kept for this coordinate.\n2. Adjust or bypass the Jacoco/dynamic-access coverage path for source-only artifacts like `accessors-smart:2.4.3`, since the tests themselves appear to pass after the workaround.\n3. Rerun the coordinate after that change and confirm both the Gradle test logs and `stats/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/execution-metrics.json` finish successfully."}}
